## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of data and the inherent biases in the sources reviewed. The ethical considerations of doctors striking are context-dependent and may vary significantly across different healthcare systems and cultural settings. Additionally, the impact of strikes on patient outcomes is complex and may not be fully captured by existing studies. Further research is needed to explore the long-term effects of strikes on healthcare delivery and patient trust.